<div id="review_2078560811" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2078560811" />
    <a title="Misstdennis" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41744660-misstdennis"><img alt="Misstdennis" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611114611p2/41744660.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2078560811?book_show_action=true">Aug 17, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Misstdennis" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Misstdennis" href="/user/show/41744660-misstdennis">Misstdennis</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780141375632" href="/book/show/32887579-one-of-us-is-lying">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41744660-misstdennis?shelf=owned-books">owned-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41744660-misstdennis?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2078560811" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16600177749826659431"><b> 5 Stars!</b><br/><br/><i>“Unless one of us is lying. Which is always a possibility.”</i><br/><br/>Oh me oh my, this book was not what I expected at all.<br/>I hadn&apos;t looked into the plot too much so I was going in half blind in a way.<br/>I was thinking this would be <b>The Breakfast Club 2.0</b>. <br/><i>But I was wrong.</i><br/>I thought this was going to be yet <b>another YA Contemporary novel with predictable plots</b>.<br/><i>But I was wrong.</i><br/><br/>This book was so gripping and I flew through the pages like it was no tomorrow.<br/>From start to finish I was on the edge of my seat</span>
  <span id="freeText16600177749826659431" style="display:none"><b> 5 Stars!</b><br><br><i>“Unless one of us is lying. Which is always a possibility.”</i><br><br>Oh me oh my, this book was not what I expected at all.<br>I hadn't looked into the plot too much so I was going in half blind in a way.<br>I was thinking this would be <b>The Breakfast Club 2.0</b>. <br><i>But I was wrong.</i><br>I thought this was going to be yet <b>another YA Contemporary novel with predictable plots</b>.<br><i>But I was wrong.</i><br><br>This book was so gripping and I flew through the pages like it was no tomorrow.<br>From start to finish I was on the edge of my seat and trying to figure out the murder like a was on an episode of Law and Order.<br>And if I'm going to toot my own horn here, I figured out who the culprit was around the half way mark.<br><i>Detective Taylor, at your service. </i><br>But in saying that, the way the plot was constructed still left me surprised by the end of the book.<br><i>So sneaky...</i><br><br>I will mention that this story heavily focuses around <b>harassment</b>, <b>mental abuse</b> and <b>homophobia</b>.<br>So if you're quite sensitive around these topics, just be mindful. <br><br>I try and make all my reviews <b>spoiler free</b> as it's just easier for review purposes <i>(who am I kidding? I'm just lazy lol)</i> So I won't go into too much detail.<br>But the story focuses heavily on 4 Students:<br><b>Bronwyn</b>, <b>Cooper</b>, <b>Nate</b> and <b>Addy</b>. And like the Breakfast club, they are all completely different students but unlike The Breakfast Club, they turn to each other for support because they have all been involved in a murder they have just witnessed together.<br>And let me just say, these students were so fantastic.<br><br><i>“I guess we're almost friends now, or as friendly as you can get when you're not one hundred percent sure the other person isn't framing you for murder.” </i><br><br>I really connected with them and my heart got heavy for them in so many ways.<br>I was angry, upset, excited and felt that I was going to burst into confetti at any given moment.<br><br>I think <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/15127507.Karen_M__McManus" title="Karen M. McManus" rel="nofollow noopener">Karen M. McManus</a> did a fantastic job with this book.<br>The style of writing, the plot with all the twist and turns that left me guessing in most parts, was just <b>SO GOOD MAN!</b><br>Kudos to you, Karen! <br><br>I'll be thinking about this book <i>(especially the ending because fuck man, I almost died. Twice.)</i> and will pick this book up again in the future.<br>So if you're yet to read this and in the mood for a bit of teenage mystery. Pick it up. You'll thank me later...<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1482557082ra/21527613.gif" width="400" height="240" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
  <a data-text-id="16600177749826659431" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


